## 12. Gap Analysis (Prioritized)

### CRITICAL (Must Fix — Production Risk)

| # | Gap | Description | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|---|
| C1 | **No rate limiting** | Login and all public endpoints are vulnerable to brute force and abuse | Add express-rate-limit middleware: 5 attempts/min for login, 100 req/min for public APIs |
| C2 | **No database transactions** | Journal entries, order activation, and cashup operations perform multiple writes without transaction isolation | Implement Supabase RPC functions or use BEGIN/COMMIT for critical multi-table writes |
| C3 | **No request audit logging** | No record of who performed what action and when — critical for a financial system | Add audit log table + middleware that logs user, action, entity, timestamp |
| C4 | **Extension race conditions** | public-extend.ts modifies multiple tables without locking | Use SELECT FOR UPDATE or RPC with transaction isolation |
| C5 | **No backup/restore strategy** | No documented database backup procedures | Configure Supabase PITR (Point-in-Time Recovery) and regular backup exports |

### HIGH (Should Fix — Significant Impact)

| # | Gap | Description | Recommendation |
|---|---|---|---|
| H1 | **Permission model too coarse** | View permissions allow write operations (expenses, maintenance, transfers, todo) | Split into can_view_* and can_edit_* for each module |
| H2 | **No pagination** | All list endpoints return unbounded result sets | Add limit/offset or cursor-based pagination to all GET collection endpoints |
| H3 | **Mixed data access patterns** | Some routes use repositories, others call Supabase directly | Standardize: ALL data access through domain ports/repositories |
| H4 | **No integration tests** | No test files detected in the repository | Add integration tests for critical flows (order lifecycle, cashup, payroll) |
| H5 | **No health check endpoint** | No /health or /status endpoint for monitoring | Add health check that verifies database connectivity |
| H6 | **PIN authentication weakness** | No expiration on PINs, no complexity requirements, no account lockout | Add PIN complexity rules, rotation policy, and lockout after N failed attempts |
| H7 | **Google Sheets dependency** | Legacy Google Sheets sync creates a fragile integration point | Plan migration path to fully eliminate Google Sheets dependency |
| H8 | **No HTTPS enforcement** | No Strict-Transport-Security or HTTPS redirect middleware | Add HSTS header and enforce HTTPS in production |

